Tullow Oil Seeks to Buy More Shares in Ghana Oil Field, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-27T22:31:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/tullow-oil-seeks-to-buy-more-shares-in-ghana-oil-field-ft-says.html
Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  is seeking to buy a
further 3.5 percent stake in Ghana’s offshore Jubilee field for
$300 million, the Financial Times reported, citing unidentified
industry officials in Ghana and  London .  The shares are controlled by EO Group, associates of
Ghana’s former president John Kufuor, the newspaper said, citing
the officials.  Tullow Oil confirmed it was in preliminary talks to
purchase the shares, which would raise its stake in the oil
field to close to 26.5 percent, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 